(62, 'admin', 'Manggala', '17,20,', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Organic rice is rice produced through an organic cultivation\r\nprocess without using chemical fertilizers and pesticides. While the organic\r\nprocess is cultivation in soils that are environmentally friendly, do not use\r\nfertilizers and chemical pesticides. This process will regulate environmental\r\nsustainability and the balance of the ecosystem that is owned. The process of\r\norganic rice cultivation is carried out using organic fertilizers, such as\r\ncompost, green fertilizers and biological fertilizers. For the eradication of\r\npests using natural pesticides produced from leaves and fruits that are\r\nfermented naturally. Organic processes can improve soil structure and\r\nfertility, and build managed ecosystems. Organic processes can also control\r\npests (OPT). Organic rice is produced from: Local (non-GMO) rice Cultivated without\r\npesticides Use organic fertilizer Use water that is not polluted Processed\r\nwithout poles (without preservatives) Compared to non-organic rice, organic\r\nrice has more advantages in: When cooked, organic rice tastes better. Rice does\r\nnot spoil quickly. Hold for up to 24 hours. More volume compared to non-organic\r\nrice. Besides having several advantages above, eating organic rice will benefit\r\nthe body, including: By consuming organic rice will reduce blood urea levels\r\nthat have accumulated up to now due to consumption of rice that is fertilized\r\nwith urea. Can reduce heavy metals in use due to chemical insecticides. Things\r\nthat can prevent the body attacked by various dangerous diseases in the last\r\ndecade suffered by many people. Organic rice has high nutritional and mineral\r\ncontent, reserves and easy to decompose protein, making it safe and very good\r\nfor diabetics. Organic rice is good for a diet program, preventing cancer,\r\nheart attacks, gout, high blood pressure and vertigo.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', 8000, 15000, 5, '50kg,25kg,20kg,15